&lt;h3&gt;Yom Yerushalayim&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;General Notes&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Yom Yerushalayim celebrates the reunification of Jerusalem during the Six Day War in 1967. Some congregations recite Hallel as well as additional Psalms and readings during services. Possible liturgy could include the readings in Mishkan T&#039;filah for Yom Ha&#039;atzm&#039;ut, beginning on page 538.&lt;/p&gt;
